consistent academic performance improvement. ARK is not a regular tuition center. It is a system-based academic institute focused on concept clarity, testing, and performance tracking. 2. Courses Offered ARK Learning Arena offers the following programs: • NEET Coaching Program • NEET Repeaters Batch • School Tuition Program (Classes 6–12) • Foundation Program (Classes 8–10) • ARK Nestlings Program Each program is designed with a structured academic system, regular testing, and personalized mentoring. 3. NEET Coaching Program The NEET Coaching Program is a 2-year intensive program for students in Class 11 and 12. Key features: • NCERT-based curriculum • Designed for 600+ NEET score • Weekly chapter-wise tests • Monthly full-length mock exams • Personalized mentoring • Small batch size (15–20 students) The program focuses on Physics, Chemistry, and Biology integration with strong emphasis on previous year questions and application-based learning. 4. NEET Repeaters Batch This program is designed for students who are re-attempting NEET. Key features: • Gap analysis of previous performance • Weak area correction • Intensive test-based training • Strategy refinement This program helps students improve their scores through focused preparation. 5. School Tuition Program ARK provides tuition for students from Class 6 to 12. Supported boards: • CBSE • ICSE • State Board Teaching approach: • Concept-based learning • Weekly assessments • Regular revision • Remedial sessions for weak students 6. Foundation Program The Foundation Program is designed for students in Classes 8 to 10. Objectives: • Build strong basics in Science and Mathematics • Prepare students early for competitive exams • Develop analytical thinking and problem-solving skills This program gives students an early advantage for NEET preparation. 7. ARK Nestlings Program This program is designed for younger students who need structured academic support. Focus areas: • Academic readiness • Basic learning skills • Foundational development 8. Teaching Methodology (5-Pillar System) ARK follows a structured 5-pillar teaching system: Diagnostic Assessment Initial evaluation of the student’s academic level Structured Academic Planning Planned syllabus completion strategy Weekly Testing Regular tests for consistent learning Performance Analytics Data-driven analysis of student performance Parent Reporting Monthly reports on progress, attendance, and scores 9. Batch Structure ARK maintains small batch sizes of 15–20 students. Benefits: • Individual attention • Better doubt clarification • Personalized mentoring 10. Assessment System ARK conducts multiple types of assessments: • Weekly chapter tests • Monthly full-length tests • Diagnostic entry test Purpose: • Identify weak areas • Track progress • Improve exam readiness 11. Academic Diagnostic Assessment (ADA) ADA is the primary entry point for all students.", "tf": {"ark": 12, "learning": 9, "arena": 4, "knowledge": 1, "base": 1, "rag": 1, "layer": 1, "premier": 1, "coaching": 4, "institute": 3, "based": 6, "chennai": 1, "established": 1, "2015": 1, "focuses": 2, "structured": 5, "academic": 9, "improvement": 2, "disciplined": 1, "systems": 1, "mentored": 1, "500": 1, "students": 13, "known": 1, "consistent": 2, "performance": 5, "regular": 4, "tuition": 4, "center": 1, "system": 5, "focused": 2, "concept": 2, "clarity": 1, "testing": 3, "tracking": 1, "courses": 1, "offered": 1, "offers": 1, "following": 1, "programs": 1, "neet": 8, "program": 17, "repeaters": 2, "batch": 5, "school": 2, "classes": 3, "12": 3, "foundation": 3, "10": 3, "nestlings": 2, "designed": 5, "personalized": 3, "mentoring": 3, "year": 2, "intensive": 2, "class": 2, "11": 2, "key": 2, "features": 2, "ncert": 1, "curriculum": 1, "600": 1, "score": 1, "weekly": 4, "chapter": 2, "wise": 1, "tests": 4, "monthly": 3, "full": 2, "length": 2, "mock": 1, "exams": 2, "small": 2, "size": 1, "15": 2, "20": 2, "physics": 1, "chemistry": 1, "biology": 1, "integration": 1,